SPECIAL NOTES!!!

 Certain computers may only boot up Swift Linux and antiX Linux on CD-Rs. If your computer does not boot up Swift Linux on a CD-RW, try Swift Linux on a CD-R.
 CRT users: Make sure your monitor is on when you boot up Swift Linux or antiX Linux. Do NOT turn off the monitor. If you are using a KVM switch, make sure your monitor is set for the computer booting up to Swift Linux, and do NOT switch to the other computer. If you try to boot up Swift Linux (or antiX Linux) without the monitor, things won't work properly. If you ignore this warning and find that you can't boot up properly, press Ctrl-Alt-Backspace to log in and enter the command &quot;startx&quot; at the prompt.

Username/Password

 When you boot up with the live CD, you may be asked to enter your username and password. Enter demo for both.
 When you run Swift Linux with the live CD, you will be asked for the root/administrative password. Enter root.
 If you install Swift Linux, you will be asked to provide a username, a password for that username, and a root/administrative password.

Location
The ISO files are hosted on SourceForge, where you can also find their md5sum values and sizes.
